!!【柯林斯英汉双解大词典】

:<div>

except /ɪkˈsɛpt/

1. PREP You use except to introduce the only thing or person that a statement does not apply to, or a fact that prevents a statement from being completely true. 除…之外 

例： I wouldn't have accepted anything except a job in New York. 我当时是不会接受一份除纽约以外任何其他地方的工作的。 

2. CONJ Except is also a conjunction. 除了… 

例： Freddie would tell me nothing about what he was writing, except that it was to be a Christmas play. 弗雷迪不愿告诉我他在写什么，只说会是个圣诞剧本。 

3. PHRASE You use except or except for to introduce the only thing or person that prevents a statement from being completely true. 除了… 

例： He hadn't eaten a thing except for one forkful of salad. 除了一口沙拉，他什么都没吃。

</div>

